This file contains the V\-F\-S implementation for unix-\/like operating systems include Linux, Mac\-O\-S\-X, $\ast$\-B\-S\-D, Q\-N\-X, Vx\-Works, A\-I\-X, H\-P\-U\-X, and others.

There are actually several different V\-F\-S implementations in this file. The differences are in the way that file locking is done. The default implementation uses Posix Advisory Locks. Alternative implementations use flock(), dot-\/files, various proprietary locking schemas, or simply skip locking all together.

This source file is organized into divisions where the logic for various subfunctions is contained within the appropriate division. This file implements an object that represents a dynmaic bitmap.

A bitmap is used to record which pages of a database file have been journalled during a transaction, or which pages have the \char`\"{}dont-\/write\char`\"{} property. Usually only a few pages are meet either condition. So the bitmap is usually sparse and has low cardinality. \hypertarget{unqlite_8c_a2b16494a4b970f529fa590cf7b954120}{\index{unqlite.\-c@{unqlite.\-c}!extract\-\_\-aux\-\_\-data@{extract\-\_\-aux\-\_\-data}}
